conversion_info.description: Information about the conversion process to FAIR format.

data_source_type.description: Type of dataset (e.g., EXP for experimental data).

byte_sequence_order.description: Byte sequence order (e.g., BIG for big-endian).

imaginary_data_kind_format.description: Format of imaginary data component (e.g., REAL, CMPLX, NODATA).

x_axis_type.description: Type of X-axis data (e.g., IDX for indexed, MONO for monotonic).

y_axis_type.description: Type of Y-axis data (e.g., IDX for indexed, NODATA for 1D spectra).

z_axis_type.description: Type of Z-axis data (e.g., NODATA for 1D/2D spectra).

intensity_data_format.description: Format of real part of intensity data (e.g., D for double precision float).

imaginary_intensity_data_format.description: Format of imaginary part of intensity data (e.g., D for double precision float).

number_of_points_x_axis.description: Number of data points along the X-axis.

x_axis_minimum.description: Minimum value of the X-axis (unit defined by XUNI).

x_axis_width.description: Width (range) of the X-axis (unit defined by XUNI).

number_of_points_y_axis.description: Number of data points along the Y-axis (for 2D experiments).

y_axis_minimum.description: Minimum value of the Y-axis (unit defined by YUNI).

y_axis_width.description: Width (range) of the Y-axis (unit defined by YUNI).

title.description: Title of the experiment or dataset.

intensity_axis_name_real.description: Name of the real part of the intensity (ordinate) axis.

intensity_axis_name_imaginary.description: Name of the imaginary part of the intensity (ordinate) axis.

intensity_axis_unit_real.description: Unit of the real part of the intensity (ordinate) axis.

intensity_axis_unit_imaginary.description: Unit of the imaginary part of the intensity (ordinate) axis.

operator_name.description: Name or identifier of the operator.

sample_form.description: Description of the sample's form or preparation.

sample_stage_temperature.description: Sample stage or temperature controller setting. Assumed Kelvin, verify units.

experiment_type.description: Type of experiment (e.g., CW for Continuous Wave, PLS for Pulsed).

ordinate_axis_1_source.description: Source/type for the first ordinate axis (e.g., IADC - Imaginary ADC signal, TADC - Transient ADC).

abscissa_axis_1_type.description: Type/parameter for the first abscissa axis (e.g., B0VL - Magnetic Field).

abscissa_axis_2_type.description: Type/parameter for the second abscissa axis (if used).

abscissa_axis_3_type.description: Type/parameter for the third abscissa axis (if used).

abscissa_1_center.description: Center value for the first abscissa axis. Units depend on AXS1 (e.g., Tesla if B0VL).

abscissa_1_sweep_width.description: Sweep width for the first abscissa axis. Units depend on AXS1 (e.g., Tesla if B0VL).

number_of_averages_set.description: Number of averages/scans set for accumulation.

unmapped_parameters.PlsSPELGlbTxt:
;
;       AWG frequency sweep
;
;     PulseSPEL general variables, definitions & conventions
begin defs

; Variables     ; Comments:

p0   = 4       ; 90 pulse length
p1   = 16      ; 180 pulse length
p2   = 32      

pg   = 400     ; Integrator Gate Width (RESERVED)

d0   = 350     
d1   = 5000    ; separation between first two pulses

; AWG variables
af0  = -25000  ; units in MHz
af1  = 0       ; units in MHz
ap0  = 0       ;
da1  = 100     ; AWG steps


a    = 100     ; (RESERVED) number of transient averages (TRANS)
; if greater than 1024, a must be a multiple of 1024
h    = 50      ; (CONVENTION) number of shots per point (INTG and SPT)
n    = 1       ; (CONVENTION) number of sweeps to accumulate

srt  = 1000 * srtu ; (RESERVED) SRT - Shot Repetition Time (srtu=1.02 us)

b    = 300     ; off resonance center field step in Gauss
c    = 5       ; sleep delay in s for field stabilization
r    = 1       ;

w    = 800     ; (CONVENTION) Split point of sweeps (points)
; i.e. pulse separation where TWT gate pulse can be split.
dx   = 0       ; (RESERVED) 1st time scale starting value
dy   = 0       ; (RESERVED) 2nd time scale starting value
d2   = 350 ns  
d30  = 2 ns    
aa0  = 100     
aa1  = 100     
end defs

; Note:
;       Variables Marked 'RESERVED' = variable may be used for other times,
;                                       however only this variable can change
;                                        the indicated parameter.
;                                       eg. only 'a' will change the number of
;                                           transients averaged in SpecJet
unmapped_parameters.PlsSPELPrgTxt:
;
; AWG frequency sweep
;
;


begin defs             ; dimension of data array [sx,sy]
dim s[1024]
dim1 s[1024] 
dim2 s[1024,500]  
dim3 s[1024,36] 
dim4  s[1024,11]     
end defs



; phase programs for AWG
begin awg0
af0     ; frequency start [MHz]
af0             ; frequency end [MHz]
ap0             ; phase [degree]
aa0             ; amplitude [%]
0               ; shape   
end awg0


begin awg1
0               ; frequency start [MHz]
0               ; frequency end [MHz]
0               ; phase [degree]
100             ; amplitude [%]
0               ; shape    
end awg1

begin awg2
0               ; frequency start [MHz]
0               ; frequency end [MHz]
0               ; phase [degree]
100             ; amplitude [%]
0               ; shape    
end awg2

begin lists "none"
asg1 +a
bsg1 +b
end lists

begin exp "SetUp" [TRANS QUAD]

shot i=1 to a              ; accumulation loop
d9
p0 [AWG0]
d1
p1 [AWG1]
d2
p2 [AWG2]
d2
d0
dig [sg1]                       
next i                     ; end of accumulation loop

end exp


begin exp1 "NUTATION" [INTG QUAD]

totscans (n)                   ; output total number of scans
scansdone(0)         
for k=1 to n                 ; averaging loop
dx = 4                       ; set x-axis to af0 frequency
p0=4 ;
sweep x=1 to sx
shot i=1 to h              ; accumulation loop
d9
p0 [AWG0]
d1
dx
p1 [AWG1]
d2
p2 [AWG2]
d2
d0
acq [sg1]                       
next i                     ; end of accumulation loop

p0=p0+d30               ; change frequency of first pulse
dx=dx+d30
next x
scansdone (k)              ; output number of scans done
next k                       ; end of averaging loop

end exp1

begin exp2 "NUTATION 2D" [INTG QUAD]

totscans (n)                   ; output total number of scans
scansdone(0)         
for k=1 to n                 ; averaging loop

for y=1 to sy
dx = 4                       ; set x-axis to af0 frequency
p0=4 ;
sweep x=1 to sx
shot i=1 to h              ; accumulation loop
d9
p0 [AWG0]
d1
dx
p1 [AWG1]
d2
p2 [AWG2]
d2
d0
acq [sg1]                       
next i                     ; end of accumulation loop

p0=p0+d30               ; change frequency of first pulse
dx=dx+d30
next x
af0=af0+da1
next y
scansdone (k)              ; output number of scans done
next k                       ; end of averaging loop

end exp2
